Mill Harbour

Schmeme Name

3 Millharbour(Great Eastern Enterprise Centre), 6-8 South Quay Square

Site Location
Two Sites: SITE 1 Land at 3 Millharbour and SITE 2 land at 6, 7 and 8 South Quay Square, South Quay Square, London

Accommodation Schedule
Total 1619
Private 1245
Affordable 0
LAR 0
Social 267
Intermediate/ Shared Ownership 107

Planning Application
PA/20/01969

Permission Date
20-Oct-21

Construction Start
Sep-20

Scheme Progress
  • Construction on hold since Q1 2022; Phase 1 has 945 units (571 private), Phase 2 has 674 private units.
  • Affordable tenures: 163 social rent, 104 affordable rent, 107 intermediate.
  • Blocks: G1 not started (674 private), G2 under construction (256 private, 169 affordable), G3 under construction (315 private), G4 under construction (205 affordable).
  • Application PA/20/01969 permitted on 20/10/2021, total 1,619 units (1,245 private, 267 social rent, 107 intermediate).
  • First completions due in 2024.

Poplar Business Park

Scheme Name

Poplar Business Park - Manhattan Plaza

Site Location
Poplar Business Park, 10 Prestons Road, London, E14 9RL

Accommodation Schedule
Total 392
Private 321
Affordable 47
LAR 0
Social 0
Intermediate/ Shared Ownership 24

Planning Application
PA/11/03375

Permission Date
23-Sep-13

Construction Start
May-15

Scheme Progress
  • 120 of 321 private units completed in Q4 2017 and sold out in Q2 2019.
  • Remaining 222 units (201 private) bought by Bloom and TPG Angelo Gordon in Q2 2024 for industrial use.
  • JV between Bloom and TPG Angelo Gordon bought the estate for £21.5m on 10 May 2024.
  • Phases 2 and 3 start date and developer not confirmed; leases expire in 2025.
  • Affordable tenures: 47 affordable rent, 24 intermediate.

Poplar Transformer Station

Scheme Name

Accommodation Schedule
Total 65
Private 0
Affordable 65
LAR 0
Social 0
Intermediate/ Shared Ownership 0

Planning Application
PA/17/00732

Permission Date
26-Feb-18

Construction Start
Sep-19

Scheme Progress
  • Construction commenced in Q3 2019 for 65 affordable units.
  • Work has been on hold since a crane collapse on 08/07/2020.
  • Full planning permission granted on 26 Feb 2018 (PA/17/00732).
  • Borough resolved to grant application on 11 Oct 2017; s106 not signed.
  • Application submitted on 22 Mar 2017 for redevelopment of three residential blocks with 65 dwellings and associated amenities.

Bow River Village

Scheme Name

Bow River Village

Site Location
Site At Bromley by Bow North, Hancock Road, London

Accommodation Schedule
Total 741
Private 667
Affordable 74
LAR 0
Social 0
Intermediate/ Shared Ownership 0

Planning Application
PA/11/02423

Permission Date
27-Sep-12

Construction Start
Nov-14

Scheme Progress
  • Phase 1 is complete, sold out/rented, and contained 145 private units and 35 affordable.
  • Phase 2 is 112 units, 73 of which are private, sold out and completed during Q1 2020.
  • 449 private units have yet to commence in future phases.
  • Phase 3 was subject to application 19/00477/FUL for 435 units, including 224 private, but that was refused on 09/04/2021.
  • Southern Housing transferred the site between companies on 30/03/2023 at a stated value of £9.86m.

Permission Date

Construction Start
Aug-22

Scheme Progress
  • Construction was put on hold during Q4 2022.
  • Two planning amendments approved in 2024: reducing top floor height and affordable housing.
  • Signs of remobilisation on site at the end of Q4 2024.
  • Taylor Wimpey launched the scheme in Sep 2022.
  • The site was bought by Taylor Wimpey in Sep 2020.

Glacier Point

Scheme Name

Glacier Point, Peterly Business Centre

Site Location
Peterley Business Centre, 472 Hackney Road, London

Accommodation Schedule
Total 218
Private 167
Affordable 33
LAR 0
Social 0
Intermediate/ Shared Ownership 18

Planning Application
PA/13/02722

Permission Date
31-Mar-15

Construction Start
Aug-15

Scheme Progress
  • Phase 1 was 55 units, sold out during Q1 2018, completed during Q3 2017.
  • The site for the remaining 167 units in Phase 2 remains partly in use as a shabby industrial estate.
  • No further action on planning or construction fronts since Phase 1 sold out.
  • Possibly the design is now so old that the next step would be a total re-plan.
  • The affordable tenures are 33 affordable rent and 17 shared ownership.

Scheme Progress
